<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9023> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9023" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 747, footnote 271" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8390> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8390" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 77, and 75, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8384> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8384" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Propraetor (Act. Tr. for 88). See 90, Praetors." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7140> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7140" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 79. Pr. 90? Badian suggests that in this period of prolonged provincial commands his praetorship and his command may have been as early as 93 and 92, respectively. Sardinia is a probable praetorian province, especially if Sextilius was in Africa before 88. See[196] Badian, Studies 82-84. Procos. Cilicia, 78-74. In MRR 2.99, 75 B.C., refer also to Alan S. Hall, New Light on the Capture of Isaura Vetus by P. Servilius Vatia, Akten des VI. Internaz. Kongr. fèr gr. u. lat. Epig. 568-571, on an inscription discovered at Bozkir with the name and title Servilius C. f. Imperator, the phrase Isaura vetere capta, and evidence of Roman use of evocatio there.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6024> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6024" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "He died early in the summer before his son's return from Asia (Cic. Phil. 2.12; Fam. 16.23.2; Dio 45.16.1-2; Jerome Chr. ad ann. 44, p. 157 Helm; Suidas 1.1.580B)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5179> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5179" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "CIL 12.2.766; Cic. Att. 4.9. 1, and 11. 2; on Valerius, Inscr. Ital. 13.3. 77; Val. Max. 2.9.9; 9. 14.5; Plin. NH 7.55; and on Servilius, Val. Max. 8.5.6. See Degrassi 132, 494f. After a destructive flood in 54 they attempted to regulate the stream of the Tiber (CIL 12.2.766 a-t; cf. Dio 39.61.1-2). They were still in office in July 54 (Cic. Att. 4.17.7), but did not complete the lustrum." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5116> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5116" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Dom. 123 and 132." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5115> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5115" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The full list of the college of Pontifices, including the Flamen Martialis and the Flamen Quirinalis (no Flamen Dialis had been inaugurated since the death of Merula in 87) and the Pontifices Minores, as it was composed on September 29, 57, can be reconstructed from Cic. Har. Resp. 12:" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4432> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4432" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Cilicia, whence he returned to celebrate his triumph (Cic. Pis. 58; Verr. 2.1.57, and 5.66; Val. Max. 8.5.6; Eutrop. 6.3, and 5; Ruf. Fest. 12.3; Claudian In Eutrop. 1.217; Ps.-Ascon. 237 Stangl; see Degrassi 564), and display his prisoners and booty (CIL 12.2.741–ILS 36; Cic. Verr. 2.1.56-57)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4393> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4393" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Cilicia (see 78-76, Promagistrates). In 75 may be placed his advance across the Taurus and reduction of the Isaurians on the northern slopes (Cic. Verr. 2.3.211; Leg. Agr. 2.50; Phil. 11.33; Att. 6.1.16; Sall. Hist. 2.82-87M; Liv. Per. 93; Strabo 12.6.2, 568c; 14.3.3, 665 c; Frontin. Str. 3.7.1; Flor. 1.41.5; Eutrop. 6.3; Ruf. Fest. 12.3; Ampel. 23; Amm. Marc. 14.8.4; Oros. 5.23.22). He was acclaimed Imperator (CIL 12.2.741; Cic. Verr. 2.1.56, and4.82; Rab. Perd. 21; Flacc. 6), and took the cognomen Isauricus (CIL 12.2.741;Fast. Cap. on 79B.C.; Ovid Fast. 1.593; Strabo 12.6.2, 568c; Vell. 2.39.2; Val. Max. 8.5.6; Eutrop. 6.3; Schol. Gron. 347 Stangl)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4326> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4326" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "6 Ormerod (JRS 12 [1922] 44) concludes from Nonius' citation of the fragment of Sall. Hist. 2.81 M from Book 2 that these operations continued into 76. See reference to Magie, above." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4325> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4325" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Cilicia (see 78, Promagistrates). To this year and the next should probably be assigned his naval victories and his occupation of the Lycian and the Pamphylian coasts (Cic. Verr. 2.1.56, and 3.210-211, and 4.21, and 5.66 and 79; Leg. Man. 68; Leg. Agr. 1.5; 2.50; Sall. Hist. 1. 128-132 M; 2.81 M; Liv. Per. 90; Strabo 14.5.7, 6710, of. 14.2 and 4, 665e; Vell. 2.39.2; App. Mith. 93; Flor. 1.41.4-5; Eutrop. 6.3; Oros. 5.23.21-22; Ruf. Fest. 11.1, and 12.3; Ammian. Marc. 14.8.4; Ps.-Ascon. 237 Stangl; Schol. Gron. 347 Stangl). See Magie, Roman Rule in Asia Minor 1.287-290; 2.1167f., note 18-19." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4299> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4299" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proconsul in Cilicia (Cic. Verr. 2.3.210-211; Liv. Per. 90, and 93; Suet. Iul. 3; Eutrop. 6.3, ex consule; Oros. 5.23.21; Ruf. Fest. 11.1, and 12.3; Ammian. Marc. 14.8.4; of. Sall. Hist. 1.127M). See 77-74, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4298> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4298" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "5 Eutropius (6.3) and Orosius (5.23.22) refer to the campaigns of Servilius Vatia Isauricus as a three year war. Orinerod (JRS 12 [1922] 37 ff.) is probably correct in supposing that 78 was given up to preparations (cf. Flor. 1.41.4) while the main operations were carried through in 77 to 75. See Magie, Roman Rule in Asia Minor 1.287-290; 2.1166-1173, notes 17-25." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4255> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4255" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap., Degrassi 54f., 130, 484f. (Servilius' name entire; AP. C ----- ]); Frontin. Str. 4.5.1 (Glaucia emended to Claudio); App. BC 1.103; Gran. Lic. 39B; Chr. 354 (Vatio et Pulchro); Fast. Hyd. (Vitia et Pulehro, Claudio et Servilio), so also Chr. Pasc.; Oros. 5.22.1; Cassiod.; Schol. Gron. 347 Stangl; on Servilius, IG 7.244; Val. Max. 8.5.6; Plut. Pomp. 14.5; Apophth. Pomp. 5; and on Claudius, Cic. Cael. 33." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4185> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4185" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably a Legate under Sulla, when with another Servilius he won an engagement near Clusium (Vell. 2.28. 1; Plut. Sull. 28.8, #)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4184> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4184" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "11 See note 10." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4048> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4048" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Driven back from Ariminum by a certain Marius (Gran. Lic. 27B; see above, on Marius Gratidianus) who took over his army." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4047> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4047" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "11 This Servilius may possibly be identified with P. Servilius Vatia (Isauricus) who celebrated a triumph in 88, and at some time joined Sulla in Greece." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3985> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3985" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Celebrated a triumph pro praetore, but from what province remains unknown (Act. Tr., Degrassi 84f., 563; see 90, Praetors). He may be identified with the Servaeus who failed of election to the consulship for 87 though supported by Sulla (Plut. Sull. 10.3; Münzer, RE, and APF 303)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3843> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3843" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "5 Servilius was a candidate for the consulship of 87 (Plut. Sull. 10.3, emending the reading #; of. Mommsen, RMW 536; Münzer, APF 303), and 90 is therefore the latest date for his praetorship under the Leges Annales. As he celebrated a triumph from his province in 88, Münzer conjeetures that he held one of the Spanish provinces, for the governors of Gaul, Macedonia, and Asia are known. All the Spanish triumphs however that are recorded in Act. Tr. were celebrated pro consule, while that of Servilius was celebrated pro praetore. The probabilities therefore favor Sardinia (of. Act. Tr. for 172) et Cilicia (see 92, Promagistrates, on Sulla), the scene of his later exploits. On his identification, see Degrassi 563. Sex. Iulius Caesar Pat. (151) Cos. 91" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3701> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3701" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Dom. 43 (ullius emended by Halm and Lange to P. Servilius). The date of his tribunate can only be conjectured from that of his praetorship, which it would normally precede by eight or more years. See Niccolini, FTP 421." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10219> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10219" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph de Isaureis. MRR II.105, Itgenshorst no. 248, Rich no. 248." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/10218> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #10218" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/30> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Triumph ex Sardinia?. MRR II.43, Itgenshorst no. 242, Rich no. 242." .
